The Debix Model A uses the following chips:
  U14A and U14B PCA9450 - NXP Power management for i.MX 8M Plus:
    "six high efficiency step-down regulators"
    "5 LDOs"
    "one 400 mA load switch"
  U8 and U12 RTL8211E - Realtek Ethernet
  U38A and U38B RTS5411S - Realtek 4 port USB Hub
  U32 SPI Flash - Not populated by default
  U33 USB Type-C - Not populated on Model A - see email on 28 July 2025
  U13 Keiiot K019 WiFi and Bluetooth
  U37 ES8316 - Everest Low power audio codec
  J801 is marked PWR on silkscreen.
  K1 is markes "RST" on silkscreen.
  K2 is marked "ON/OFF" on silkscreen.
  J1 is SD Card socket

